---
title: "Sequence Diagram: /research Skill"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant Web as Web Search
    participant FS as File System

    User->>Claude: /research <topic> [context]

    note over Claude,FS: Check existing research
    Claude->>FS: Check docs/research-<slug>.md
    FS-->>Claude: Exists / not found

    alt Report exists
        Claude->>FS: Read existing report
        FS-->>Claude: Previous findings + date
        Claude->>Claude: Plan: update with<br/>new findings
    else No existing report
        Claude->>Claude: Plan: create new report
    end

    note over Claude,Web: Search official sources
    Claude->>Web: Search official docs<br/>for <topic>
    Web-->>Claude: Official documentation
    Claude->>Claude: Extract key facts +<br/>real URLs

    note over Claude,Web: Search community sources
    Claude->>Web: Search community guides,<br/>blog posts, GitHub repos
    Web-->>Claude: Community content
    Claude->>Claude: Cross-reference across<br/>3+ sources

    note over Claude,Claude: Analyze findings
    Claude->>Claude: Structure findings into<br/>sections with specifics
    Claude->>Claude: Build gaps table<br/>with priorities
    Claude->>Claude: Write actionable<br/>recommendations

    opt Context references a skill or feature
        Claude->>FS: Read current skill/feature
        FS-->>Claude: Current implementation
        Claude->>Claude: Compare current state<br/>vs research findings
    end

    note over Claude,FS: Save report
    alt Updating existing
        Claude->>FS: Update research-<slug>.md<br/>(add findings, update date)
    else New report
        Claude->>FS: Write research-<slug>.md
    end
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    Claude->>User: Summary box with<br/>key findings, source count,<br/>gaps found, file path
